snippet: A conference meant to showcase President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi’s economic reforms also included signs of his government’s continued dependence on the monarchies that aided his rise to power.
abstract: Egyptian Pres Abdel Fattah el-Sisi highlights his efforts toward economic reform during three-day development conference, but some businessmen complain that government has still done too little to clear away obstacles to growth.

byline.original: By DAVID D. KIRKPATRICK and MERNA THOMAS

lead_paragraph: A conference meant to showcase President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi’s economic reforms also included signs of his government’s continued dependence on the monarchies that aided his rise to power.

headline.main: Egypt’s Leader Showcases Plans for Growth
headline.print_headline: Egypt’s Leader Showcases Plans for Growth
